data.title: Saint George Church
data.text:
Learn About Our Liturgy | Frequently Asked Questions

​

St. George is a Roman Catholic Church of the Personal Ordinariate of the Chair of St. Peter, in full communion with the Diocese of Springfield-Cape Girardeau, the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops (USCCB) and the Holy See in Rome.

​

Our Lord Jesus Christ calls us to share his Gospel in the Republic area, inviting people into fellowship through the Scriptures, Tradition, and the sacraments.

​

We welcome you to discover St. George's loving and supportive community. We look forward to worshiping with you, praying with you, and spending time with you as friends united in Jesus Christ our Lord and Savior. We hope your experience at St. George feels like coming home.

​

If you would like to learn more about our Lord Jesus Christ, and his Catholic Church, just watch this video.
